      "body" : "There&#39;s really no way to make the include.NON_NULL annotation to work? Or the NON_EMTPY one?  Because I know which one will be null, but it depends on the situation. I&#39;m using the same &quot;JsonOperation&quot; class for every object that I want to serialize / deserialize and I&#39;m only initializing the variables that I need to use depending on the situation. Is this a good way to do it or I should do severals classes containing only the variables that I need (that way I wouldn&#39;t have to use any annotation, since there will never be a null/empty variable)"
