    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You have the annotation in the wrong place - it needs to be on the class, not the field. i.e: </p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonInclude(Include.NON_NULL) //or Include.NON_EMPTY, if that fits your use case \npublic static class Request {\n  // ...\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>As noted in comments, in versions below 2.x the syntax for this annotation is: </p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonSerialize(include = JsonSerialize.Inclusion.NON_NULL) // or JsonSerialize.Inclusion.NON_EMPTY\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The other option is to configure the <code>ObjectMapper</code> directly, simply by calling \n<code>mapper.setSerializationInclusion(Include.NON_NULL);</code></p>\n\n<p>(for the record, I think the popularity of this answer is an indication that this annotation <em>should</em> be applicable on a field-by-field basis, @fasterxml)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 51977,
      "reputation" : 937,
      "user_id" : 155316,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c70f66965c2007ea1fe0ecb0727fe8b3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "nomad",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/155316/nomad"
    },
